==English==

===Etymology===
From the {{L.}} ''[[malevolentia]]'', derived from ''[[malevolens|malēvolens]]'' ([[malevolent]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# [[hostile|Hostile]] attitude or feeling.
#: ''To show someone '''malevolence'''.''
#: ''He said it with '''malevolence'''.''
# Behavior exhibiting a hostile attitude.

====Synonyms====
* (''attitude or feeling'') [[ill-will]], [[malice]], [[spite]]

